    "Articlehttps://doi.org/10.1038/s41556-023-01317-3 transposase-accessible chromatin with sequencing (ATAC-Seq) 49 and performed ChIP-Seq for the trimethylation of histone H3 at K4 (H3K4me3; which flanks the transcription start sites (TSS) of active Pol II genes) 50, K27 (H3K27me3; which marks Pol II genes repressed in specific cell states) 51 and K9 (H3K9me3; which marks repeat-rich heterochromatin) 52.",
